The proposed project contains a number of activities building towards the achievement of two main components:
Component 1. Technical and institutional capacity building to plan, design, implement and maintain integrated urban Ecosystems-based Adaptation (EbA) interventions for the reduction of climate change-induced flooding; 
Component 2.  Rehabilitation and protection of ecosystem in response to climate variability and change;

Support Lao Immigration officials increased capacity and skills in detecting by using advanced and modern traveling documents control technology and identity fraud detection
-Feasibility Study and Technological Assessment of BCPs; 
-Installation of Verifier TD&B to all 29 international BCPs; 
-Verifier TD&B training of trainers; 
-Training courses including, Border and Migration Management, Travel Document Examination, Interviewing Skills, Victim Identification, and Women and Child Protection.
